{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/66830", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/66830/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/66830/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/66830/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/66830", "id": 529681854, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1Mjk2ODE4NTQ=", "number": 66830, "title": "arrays require explicit coercion to &[T]", "user": {"login": "tdyas", "id": 901363, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjkwMTM2Mw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/901363?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas", "html_url": "https://github.com/tdyas", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdyas/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2019-11-28T04:09:37Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-28T06:28:22Z", "closed_at": "2019-11-28T06:25:47Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code seems like it should compile since a coercion seems to be performed for the `insert` but not performed for the `contains_key`.\r\n\r\n```\r\nuse std::collections::HashMap;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut h: HashMap<&[u8], &[u8]> = HashMap::new();\r\n    h.insert(b\"foo\", b\"bar\");\r\n    if h.contains_key(b\"foo\") {\r\n        println!(\"YES\");\r\n    } else {\r\n        println!(\"NO\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error is:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror[E0277]: the trait bound `&[u8]: std::borrow::Borrow<[u8; 3]>` is not satisfied\r\n --> src/main.rs:6:10\r\n  |\r\n6 |     if h.contains_key(b\"foo\") {\r\n  |          ^^^^^^^^^^^^ the trait `std::borrow::Borrow<[u8; 3]>` is not implemented for `&[u8]`\r\n  |\r\n  = help: the following implementations were found:\r\n            <[T; _] as std::borrow::Borrow<[T]>>\r\n```\r\n\r\nChanging `h.contains_key(b\"foo\")` to `h.contains_key(b\"foo\" as &[u8])` fixes the error and the code works as expected. If byte literals are arrays, why is coercion to `&[u8]` done implicitly for the `insert` but not the `contains_key`?\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "csmoe", "id": 35686186, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM1Njg2MTg2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/35686186?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe", "html_url": "https://github.com/csmoe", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmoe/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/66830/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket"